03:11.414 --> 03:14.784
Oh. I'm sorry.
This is Marty Ratner. everybody.

03:14.951 --> 03:16.441
-Hi.
GROUP: Hi. Marty.

03:16.620 --> 03:18.020
We didn't mean to gawk...

03:18.188 --> 03:21.018
...it's just that we weren't aware
that Selma was....

03:21.591 --> 03:23.691
Alive?

03:24.094 --> 03:25.964
I was gonna say "involved."

03:26.129 --> 03:28.259
Remember our last date?

03:28.431 --> 03:34.201
Yes. You picked me up at 7:20
in your tan Buick.

03:34.371 --> 03:36.931
We had wine. lobster...

03:37.107 --> 03:41.637
...and danced until 3:45 in the morning.

03:42.045 --> 03:43.335
Well. isn't that--?

03:43.512 --> 03:45.782
Almost interesting.

03:45.948 --> 03:47.208
We think so.

03:47.383 --> 03:49.443
It was 45 years ago.

03:49.885 --> 03:52.715
Let's go someplace
where we can catch up.

03:52.888 --> 03:53.908
I'm all ears.

03:54.089 --> 03:57.219
That's not the way I remember it.

03:58.726 --> 04:01.216
Good evening. I'm Arnold Koppelson.

04:01.396 --> 04:04.956
-You must be our man from Brooklyn.
-And you must be Judge Harold Stone.

04:05.133 --> 04:08.663
-Wild guess?
-I never guess. I just knew.

04:08.836 --> 04:10.926
I hope you people realize
how lucky you are...

04:11.105 --> 04:13.395
...to be working with a man like this.

04:14.207 --> 04:16.937
We often hear of your talents
in the Brooklyn court.

04:17.110 --> 04:20.170
So I consider it a privilege
and an honor to sit on your bench...

04:20.346 --> 04:21.637
...even for a brief session.

04:21.814 --> 04:24.014
Well. I'll see you all in the courtroom.

04:26.419 --> 04:30.049
He was really shoveling it fast and furious.
wasn't he?

04:30.456 --> 04:33.586
Well. now. Dan. maybe he was sincere.

04:33.759 --> 04:37.389
Sincere? He made Harry
seem like the Second Coming.

04:45.771 --> 04:50.801
An unassuming little burgundy
you might find amusing.

04:53.379 --> 04:56.279
Red with Jell-O?

05:00.086 --> 05:03.776
-So that was your third husband.
-Yes.

05:04.723 --> 05:06.883
But the one you left at the toll plaza--

05:07.057 --> 05:08.117
Number five.

05:09.293 --> 05:11.693
I thought five was the contortionist.

05:11.862 --> 05:13.132
Oh. that was Phil.

05:13.297 --> 05:15.787
The one who drove with his feet?

05:15.966 --> 05:17.486
He ate with them too.

05:18.868 --> 05:22.698
I stayed away from carnivals after that.

05:23.338 --> 05:24.358
All rise.

05:26.074 --> 05:28.244
Criminal court part two
is now in session.

05:28.409 --> 05:30.379
The Honorable...

05:31.278 --> 05:33.868
..."Arno|d Koppe|son"...

05:34.581 --> 05:36.311
...presiding.

05:36.949 --> 05:38.209
You may be seated.

05:40.853 --> 05:43.353
Oh. and. bailiff. may I just say...

05:43.522 --> 05:46.462
...that having a presence
as strong as yours in the courtroom...

05:46.625 --> 05:48.215
...is reassuring.
to say the least.

05:49.293 --> 05:51.763
-Thank you. sir.
-Your welcome.

06:00.438 --> 06:03.138
-Here's tonight's docket. sir.
-Oh. thank you.

06:03.307 --> 06:04.777
What a pleasant man.

06:04.942 --> 06:07.972
Yeah. I don't trust him either.

06:08.478 --> 06:10.668
People v. Milo Wright.

06:10.847 --> 06:13.007
-Your Honor. Mr. Wright was arrested--
ARNOLD: |....

06:13.182 --> 06:16.052
I read your report. Mr. Fielding.
I know all about it.

06:16.218 --> 06:18.518
-Merely trying to be helpful. sir.
-No need.

06:18.686 --> 06:20.376
Your sense of accuracy is uncanny...

06:20.555 --> 06:22.915
...and your attention to detail
is extraordinary.

06:23.091 --> 06:26.121
It virtually jumps off the paper.

06:27.528 --> 06:29.588
Uh-- W-w-well. thank you. sir.

06:29.963 --> 06:32.733
And you say
you're only an assistant DA. huh?

06:33.333 --> 06:35.703
You know. frankly. Mr. Fielding.
that stuns me...

06:35.869 --> 06:39.999
...but I'm sure it's just an oversight that
will be corrected in the very near future.

06:40.174 --> 06:42.234
Your Honor. I...

06:43.143 --> 06:45.133
...love you.

06:47.247 --> 06:51.177
