Mac. go get me the cases
that Koppelson ruled on.

10:28.219 --> 10:30.519
-All of them?
-Well. how many are there?

10:30.687 --> 10:31.807
Eighty-four.

10:31.988 --> 10:33.548
In less than three hours?

10:33.723 --> 10:35.623
I'm telling you. Harry. the guy is--

10:35.792 --> 10:38.782
Amazing. incredible. the best.
Yeah. I remember.

10:38.962 --> 10:41.452
All right. I'm going.
I'll help Mac with the cases.

10:41.631 --> 10:45.361
Right. Use a forklift if you have to.

10:50.106 --> 10:52.336
Well. where's my lecture?

10:52.509 --> 10:55.599
-Lecture?
-About running off to Miami...

10:55.779 --> 11:00.809
...with a man I haven't seen
since the Louisiana Purchase.

11:01.451 --> 11:02.891
Selma...

11:03.053 --> 11:05.583
...now. you know we all care about you.

11:05.755 --> 11:08.655
You can't walk in here
and tell us you're moving to Florida...

11:08.825 --> 11:10.985
...and not expect us to be concerned.

11:11.493 --> 11:13.023
Well. be quick about it. Harry...

11:13.194 --> 11:16.654
...because I've got decades
to make up for tonight.

11:17.732 --> 11:18.762
Se|ma....

11:19.133 --> 11:20.433
Save it. Harry.

11:20.600 --> 11:24.260
I'm cresting on a wave of love.

11:24.438 --> 11:25.698
That bad. huh?

11:25.872 --> 11:28.242
He makes my elbows sweat.

11:28.909 --> 11:30.669
I get the picture.

11:32.212 --> 11:33.272
Selma...

11:36.716 --> 11:37.736
...be careful.

11:38.685 --> 11:41.345
Would I disappoint you?

11:47.027 --> 11:50.857
Hey. it could have happened to anybody.

11:52.264 --> 11:54.604
Judge Stone.
your bailiff said there was a problem.

11:54.767 --> 11:57.457
I'm afraid there is. Arnold.
Where did you find him. Bull?

11:57.636 --> 12:01.536
Dan's favorite restaurant. La Pretense.

12:03.242 --> 12:04.542
What the hell is going on?

12:04.709 --> 12:08.239
Bigfoot comes barging into the restaurant.
practically drags us out.

12:08.413 --> 12:10.073
Why don't you tell him. Arnold?

12:11.648 --> 12:15.278
I talked to your supervisor.
I know who you are.

12:17.421 --> 12:19.751
Who are he?

12:19.923 --> 12:21.083
Arnold?

12:24.193 --> 12:27.323
I'm a clerk in the Record Division
over at Brooklyn court.

12:29.030 --> 12:31.330
A clerk?

12:31.899 --> 12:32.919
I'm afraid so.

12:33.100 --> 12:35.300
I promised you could be godfather
to my first...

12:35.469 --> 12:38.029
...and you're telling me you're a clerk?

12:38.205 --> 12:43.035
I suppose this puts our ski weekend
in Vermont on the back burner. doesn't it?

12:49.215 --> 12:50.975
Lobsters and wine.

12:51.151 --> 12:53.091
What else?

12:58.658 --> 13:00.488
This is moving.

13:00.660 --> 13:01.750
Thank you.

13:01.928 --> 13:03.448
I meant the lobster.

13:03.629 --> 13:04.859
[LAUGHS]

13:05.763 --> 13:10.033
Julia taught me how to pack them live
right from the dock.

13:10.201 --> 13:12.071
The cook is boiling the water.

13:12.737 --> 13:14.567
-Julia?
-That's my wife's name.

13:15.273 --> 13:18.143
I brought them up from Florida with me
on the plane.

13:18.309 --> 13:19.829
They got a window seat. Ha-ha-ha.

13:20.343 --> 13:21.833
A window seat. Ha-ha-ha.

13:22.913 --> 13:25.513
You were always a tough audience.

13:26.015 --> 13:28.275
So. what's the plan?

13:29.084 --> 13:33.994
We pack your things.
we fly to Fort Lauderdale. we go crazy.

13:34.156 --> 13:37.676
I like it.
Is your place near the courthouse?

13:37.860 --> 13:40.020
Maybe there is some job openings.

13:40.195 --> 13:41.655
Ha-ha. Job openings?

13:41.829 --> 13:45.599
Why on earth would you want a job?
I've got plenty of money.

13:45.767 --> 13:48.127
It's not the money. I like to work.

13:48.703 --> 13:50.033
Julia never did.

13:50.405 --> 13:53.525
-Marty....
-Excuse me. is this the Ratner party?

13:53.708 --> 13:54.728
Yes.

13:54.909 --> 13:56.999
I was told to play for two people in love.

13:57.178 --> 13:58.168
Enjoy-

