14:02.817 --> 14:05.717
Wait. wait. wait a minute.
there must be some mistake.

14:05.887 --> 14:08.317
I ordered a violin player.

14:08.489 --> 14:11.319
He had to cancel. so they sent me.

14:11.492 --> 14:13.322
Please don't ask me to leave.

14:13.494 --> 14:16.334
Everybody asks me to leave.

14:16.598 --> 14:19.798
If you ask me to leave.
I'm going to take the elevator to the roof...

14:19.968 --> 14:22.268
...and plunge to my death.

14:22.703 --> 14:26.373
Just make sure you take that with you.

14:27.441 --> 14:30.601
-Mister?
-Well. I suppose it'll be okay.

14:31.311 --> 14:33.251
I owe you my life.

14:33.880 --> 14:36.510
Just keep it soft and romantic.

14:37.084 --> 14:38.114
Got it.

14:38.285 --> 14:40.275
[PLAYS SLOW MILITARY TUNE]

14:42.489 --> 14:44.979
Lovely. I mean that.

14:46.627 --> 14:48.527
Listen. Marty.

14:48.695 --> 14:50.955
Hold it a minute. chucko.

14:51.598 --> 14:52.998
I'll tell you when.

14:54.201 --> 14:56.641
Selma.
I know you've enjoyed your job up here.

14:56.803 --> 14:59.743
But why should you work
when I can take care of you?

14:59.906 --> 15:01.126
Julia never worked.

15:01.307 --> 15:04.827
What did she do all day. pack seafood?

15:06.112 --> 15:08.412
She used to knit me things.

15:08.580 --> 15:10.740
She made me soufflÃ©s.

15:10.914 --> 15:12.444
Cleaned the house.

15:12.615 --> 15:15.945
She had aprons from all 50 states.

15:16.119 --> 15:18.379
Marty. listen to me.

15:18.554 --> 15:23.824
I don't knit. I don't cook.
I don't clean houses.

15:23.992 --> 15:27.022
-That's why God gave us other people.
-Ha-ha.

15:27.428 --> 15:30.158
[LAUGHING]
Selma. you're a scream.

15:30.331 --> 15:34.891
Now. seriously. I know that you'll enjoy
not having the grind of a daily job.

15:35.069 --> 15:37.299
Please. let me take care of you.

15:37.471 --> 15:40.741
Oh. and in return. I take care of you?

15:41.108 --> 15:43.238
Isn't that what love is all about?

15:43.411 --> 15:45.401
IRESUMES PLAYING]

15:46.514 --> 15:49.684
Not yet. Not yet.

15:50.451 --> 15:53.281
Sorry. The moment moved me.

15:54.988 --> 15:57.688
-Marty.
-Yes. lamb chop?

15:57.857 --> 16:01.377
Marty. maybe we'd better hold off
on that jet.

16:01.795 --> 16:03.625
What are you talking about?

16:03.797 --> 16:06.357
Sounds like dump city. pal.

16:06.833 --> 16:10.933
Leave or scarlet bellows
will start to spread.

16:12.237 --> 16:15.367
My father made me take lessons.

16:15.541 --> 16:17.641
God will punish him.

16:22.614 --> 16:27.454
You had us. accomplished attorneys.
practicing law in front of you...

16:27.618 --> 16:31.248
...a clerk charading as a magistrate.
for almost three hours.

16:32.223 --> 16:35.163
You have made a mockery
out of this country's justice system.

16:35.326 --> 16:37.286
And you have nothing to say
for yourself?

16:38.730 --> 16:41.060
I enjoyed the rack of lamb.

16:41.232 --> 16:44.172
I want it back. It's mine.

16:44.335 --> 16:47.665
Now. what is this nonsense
about not going away with me?

16:47.839 --> 16:50.269
Listen to yourself. Marty.
You don't want me.

16:50.441 --> 16:52.241
You want a domestic.

16:52.410 --> 16:56.210
What you and Julia had all these years
was great.

16:56.381 --> 16:58.371
But it's not my kind of great.

16:59.283 --> 17:02.153
Selma. I never thought of you as a maid.

17:02.320 --> 17:03.880
I thought of you as a woman.

17:04.055 --> 17:05.484
I know. doll.

17:05.656 --> 17:10.086
But I just don't think
I'm quite what you have in mind.

17:10.261 --> 17:12.461
You're used to something else.

17:16.334 --> 17:18.204
I guess I am.

17:18.368 --> 17:20.358
I always was a little helpless.

17:20.805 --> 17:24.605
You made the right choice
in 1938. Marty.

17:24.776 --> 17:28.205
I'm sure I could bring myself
to change a little.

17:28.378 --> 17:29.809
Maybe we both can.

17:29.981 --> 17:32.611
-Marty--
-Did I mention the double gas oven?

17:33.050 --> 17:36.850
I use mine to dry my pantyhose.

17:38.322 --> 17:39.852
I see what you mean.

17:42.591 --> 17:47.121
Listen. I know how you all must be feeling.
and I can't blame you for being angry.

17:47.296 --> 17:49.586
But I fully expected to go to jail.

17:49.764 --> 17:51.364
You knew this was gonna happen?

17:51.532 --> 17:54.262
Sure. I'm just surprised
that I lasted as long as I did.

17:54.435 --> 17:57.885
-Well. why did you do it?
-I always wanted to.

17:58.071 --> 18:01.531
Well. that's certainly stupid.

18:02.276 --> 18:03.636
No. not really.

18:03.810 --> 18:06.970
You see. I'm retiring next month.

18:07.346 --> 18:13.116
I used to sit at my little desk for 30 years
while the judges came and went...

18:13.286 --> 18:16.416
...night after night.
watching and waiting...

18:16.589 --> 18:19.019
...and dreaming that one day.
I'd be up there myself.

18:19.192 --> 18:22.392
And then this afternoon
when the call came for a replacement...

18:22.562 --> 18:26.592
...it occurred to me that maybe
this would be my last chance.

18:27.033 --> 18:28.803
Do you know something?

18:28.968 --> 18:32.368
Even now I get the feeling you're not
the slightest bit sorry about this.

18:32.537 --> 18:34.507
-Well. I'm not.
-Incredible.

18:35.040 --> 18:37.130
Why? I did a hell of a job.

18:37.642 --> 18:38.912
He's right.

18:39.778 --> 18:40.798
He is?

18:40.979 --> 18:44.439
As far as I'm concerned. yup.

18:44.950 --> 18:49.320
I would've made the same decision
in virtually every one of these cases.

18:49.488 --> 18:53.688
Well. the prosecution did an excellent job.
It made my work easy.

18:53.859 --> 18:55.159
-Thank you.
-You're welcome.

18:55.326 --> 18:58.186
-Geek.
-Bootlicker.

18:58.963 --> 19:02.333
Mac. I'll sign these myself later
and then you can take them downstairs.

19:02.500 --> 19:04.090
I'll finish off the night.

19:04.267 --> 19:05.387
What about this guy?

19:05.802 --> 19:08.672
Oh. don't worry about me.
I'm familiar with the prison system.

19:08.838 --> 19:10.598
I'll get along.

19:10.773 --> 19:11.873
Go home. Arnold.

19:15.210 --> 19:16.680
I beg your pardon?

19:17.145 --> 19:18.535
Go home.

19:18.714 --> 19:22.154
Putting you in jail is only gonna cost
the city money for no reason.

19:22.651 --> 19:24.211
But I committed a crime.

19:24.386 --> 19:25.816
First offense. right?

19:26.321 --> 19:27.651
Well. yes. that's true. but--

19:27.823 --> 19:31.223
"He made a mistake.
and based on my 30 years of experience...

19:31.392 --> 19:34.792
...I'm gonna take a chance
that he learned something from it."

19:35.695 --> 19:37.085
I said that. didn't I?

19:37.264 --> 19:39.604
Steven's case. It was a first offense too.

19:40.233 --> 19:43.363
Well. based on
my two years of experience...

19:43.537 --> 19:46.767
...I'm gonna take
the same chance on you. Arnold.

19:46.940 --> 19:48.570
Now. go home.

19:52.812 --> 19:54.872
Thank you. Your Honor.

19:56.449 --> 20:00.439
Oh. just so you know.
you really are big in Brooklyn.

20:01.554 --> 20:02.584
Arnold.

20:04.322 --> 20:06.192
You would've made a good judge.

20:07.125 --> 20:09.855
I was a good judge.

20:27.412 --> 20:29.382
-Hi.
-Hi.

20:30.315 --> 20:33.005
I thought
you might have thought things over.

20:33.618 --> 20:35.478
-I did.
-And?

20:36.154 --> 20:38.654
Can you picture this body in an apron?

20:39.390 --> 20:43.550
No. But I can picture it without an apron.

20:44.495 --> 20:46.085
December 12th.

20:46.263 --> 20:49.293
The observation deck
of the Empire State Building.

20:49.465 --> 20:51.185
Yeah.

20:52.167 --> 20:53.357
IEXHALESI

20:53.535 --> 20:57.055
I think we were facing north.

20:57.238 --> 20:59.498
Listen. I want you to take this.

20:59.674 --> 21:01.774
It rowed up with the lobsters.

21:01.943 --> 21:04.413
"1938."

21:05.213 --> 21:06.873
It was a very good year.

21:08.716 --> 21:10.236
See you. Selma.

21:10.617 --> 21:12.277
See you. Marty.

21:19.391 --> 21:23.091
We held the record
until the World Trade Center went up.

21:31.936 --> 21:34.736
-Hi. Selma.
-Hi. Harry.

21:35.573 --> 21:36.603
What happened?

21:37.141 --> 21:41.701
We had some wine.
killed some crustaceans...

21:41.879 --> 21:45.079
...and then some guy
played military music.

21:48.252 --> 21:52.522
-What about Marty?
-It turns out he wanted somebody else.

21:54.191 --> 21:56.681
-I'm sorry.
-No sweat.

21:56.861 --> 21:58.561
If you're interested...

21:58.729 --> 22:03.389
...and if you're wondering if a heart
can beat through nine presidents...

22:04.101 --> 22:07.801
...six husbands. 45 springs...

22:08.304 --> 22:13.944
...and still race at the sight of a tan Buick
driving up the street...

22:14.110 --> 22:16.740
...honey. I'm here to tell you it can.

22:23.353 --> 22:25.013
I'll bet it can.

22:25.187 --> 22:27.207
Oh. I've been through worse.

22:27.388 --> 22:30.588
Well. tonight. you'll be through better.

22:30.758 --> 22:32.888
Lets you and me go out after the session.

22:33.061 --> 22:34.261
Oh. don't worry about it.

22:34.429 --> 22:35.829
Come on. it'll cheer you up.

22:35.997 --> 22:38.017
Oh. seriously. I'm fine.

22:38.198 --> 22:40.498
Selma. you're not fine.

22:40.666 --> 22:43.256
MAN: Hi. Selma.
-Oh. hi. Brent.

22:43.435 --> 22:46.595
-Pick you up at 11?
-Sure.

22:47.505 --> 22:50.095
I'm looking forward to it.

22:55.813 --> 22:57.713
Your nephew.

22:58.182 --> 23:00.082
Your lawyer?

23:00.250 --> 23:02.580
Your nephew's lawyer?

23:02.753 --> 23:05.153
Your lawyer's nephew?

